RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 19000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMPETUOUS SOUL settled off the early pace while racing four wide, cruised up to the lead four wide around the far turn, drew off under a drive in upper stretch, drifted in a bit in midstretch and widened under mild urging. NOTARY SOJAC was bumped soon after the start, pressed the pace in the three path, could not match strides with the winner from the five-sixteenths marker, angled in nearing the eighth pole and won the place duel. STRAIGHT TIME stalked the pace two wide, tipped three wide near the quarter pole, could not keep pace with the winner, battled outside of NOTARY SOJAC through the stretch for the place and just missed. ON THE RUNWAY broke outwardly and bumped foes at the start, raced off the pace five wide, steadied late on the first turn, edged closer four wide around the far turn but never threatened. RULE IT failed to menace while racing two wide. TUMIGA was bumped between foes at the start, raced two and three wide in midpack and lacked a clsoing bid. DUNKLE hit the starting gate, saved ground and made little impact. KING ZAM bumped soon after the start, set the pace along the rail and faltered around the far turn. FUN AMERICAN raced three wide in midpack, steadied late on the first turn, went four wide around the far turn and never factored. PARADISE DRIVE was bumped at the start and always far back inside. BALTIC PRINCE hesitated at the start and was outrun inside. DRAMA'S GOLD chased the pace four wide and was through after a half.
